Barnes Group said it expectssales and net income for 1987 will be up slightly over 1986.    Without supplying specific figures, Barnes toldshareholders at its annual meeting it expected net income toimprove at a rate exceeding its growth in sales, which was twopct higher than 1985.    The company said it recorded income from continuingoperations of 16.6 mln dlrs, or 2.57 dlrs per share, on salesof 440 mln dlrs in 1986. It said it recorded income fromcontinuing operations of 16.4 mln dlrs, or 2.27 dlrs per share,in the previous year. Reuter&#3;